page.title: 09RYEHILL VILLAGE
page.content: APART FROM SCATTERED FARMHOUSES,AND ABOUT 30 BUNGALOWS GROUPED TOGETHER ON THE MAIN HULL TO WITHERNSEA ROAD AND KNOWN AS BRIDGE BUNGALOWS,THE MAIN AREA OF POPULATION IS THE VILLAGE OF RYEHILL. THE SMALL VILLAGE HAS A POPULATION OF APPROXIMATELY 120. THERE ARE NO SHOPS,BUT A REGULAR BUS ROUTE TO HULL OR WITHERNSEA IS AVAILABLE ON THE NEARBYE MAIN ROAD.A PUBLIC TELEPHONE IS IN THE VILLAGE. THE RESIDENTS WORK EITHER LOCALLY ON FARMS,OR COMMUTE INTO HULL. THE VILLAGE PUB IS WELL KNOWN,AND IS THE SOCIAL HUB OF VILLAGE LIFE.
